Labour Party, LP, chieftain Kenneth Okonkwo has labelled the All Progressives Congress, APC, a religious party. He made the declaration on Thursday when he appeared on Channels Television 2023 Verdict. The spokesperson of the LP Presidential Campaign Council stated the Muslim-Muslim ticket of the APC was against the provisions of the constitution. Okonkwo said the fact that the country’s laws country highlights fairness was an indication that the religion must be taken into consideration in politics and governance. He noted that APC presidential candidate, Bola Tinubu, his running mate Kashim Shettima and others top officers holders are Muslims. “The APC chairman (Abdullahi Adamu) is Muslim, the Senate President (Ahmad Lawan) is Muslim, the House of Representatives Speaker (Femi Gbajabiamila) is Muslim. “The Deputy Speaker (Ahmed Wase) is Muslim. APC is a religious party, they are religious. This is a multi-religious country,” the LP member said. Okonkwo also claimed there are plans to make Lawan and Gbajabiamila return to their positions if the ruling party retains power.